message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To refer unresolved customer grievances to designated departments, first ensure you have all necessary details about the grievance, including customer contact information, a description of the issue, and any previous communication or attempts at resolution. Then, identify the appropriate department based on the nature of the grievance, such as billing, technical support, or product quality. Use the company's internal communication system or protocol to forward the grievance details to the designated department, ensuring you include all relevant information for a thorough investigation. Finally, inform the customer that their issue has been escalated and provide them with any reference numbers or expected timelines for follow-up.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
